snail /sneɪl/

(snails) 

1. N-COUNT A snail is a small animal with a long, soft body, no legs, and a spiral-shaped shell. Snails move very slowly. 蜗牛 

2. PHRASE If you say that someone does something at a snail's pace , you are emphasizing that they are doing it very slowly, usually when you think it would be better if they did it much more quickly. 慢吞吞地 [强调] 

例： The train was moving now at a snail's pace. 火车现在正缓慢行驶。

